HOUSE BILL No. 1199
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 16-37-2-20.
Synopsis: Birth certificate information. Provides that the gender listed
on an individual's birth certificate and permanent record made from the
birth certificate may not be changed. Specifies certain exceptions.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Borders
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Public Health.
2026 IN 1199—LS 6610/DI 104

Introduced
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
PRINTING CODE. Amendments: Whenever an existing statute (or a section of the Indiana
Constitution) is being amended, the text of the existing provision will appear in this style type,
additions will appear in this style type, and deletions will appear in this style type.
Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
HOUSE BILL No. 1199
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
health.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 16-37-2-20 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
3 1, 2026]: Sec. 20. (a) Notwithstanding any other law, and except as
4 provided in subsection (b), the gender listed on an individual's:
5 (1) birth certificate; and
6 (2) permanent record made from the birth certificate under
7 section 9 of this chapter;
8 may not be changed.
9 (b) The gender listed on an individual's birth certificate and the
10 permanent record made from the birth certificate under section 9
11 of this chapter may be changed only if any of the following
12 conditions exist:
13 (1) The:
14 (A) person filing the birth certificate; or
15 (B) state department recording the information;
16 made a typographical or clerical error concerning the
17 individual's gender.
2026 IN 1199—LS 6610/DI 104

2
1 (2) The individual's gender was listed as male but a medical
2 test demonstrates the absence of a Y chromosome in the
3 individual's deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA).
4 (3) The individual's gender was listed as female but a medical
5 test demonstrates the presence of a Y chromosome in the
6 individual's deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA).
